/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  Yang 2020 polymer group contributions for the GLASS TRANSITION Tg(inf).

  Source (genuinely open, redistributable -- unlike the Van Krevelen book):
    Yang, Zou, Ye, Zhu, Dong, Bi, "A Modified Group Contribution Scheme to
    Predict Homopolymer Glass Transition Temperatures", ACS Omega 5 (2020)
    19655, doi:10.1021/acsomega.0c04499 -- CC-BY 4.0.
    Values transcribed FAITHFULLY from Supporting Information Table S3
    ("Formula weights and contributions of groups used to predict Tg(inf)",
    pp. S10-S13), fetched via the europepmc open mirror (PMC7676332).

  THE EQUATION (paper eq 5):
    Tg(inf) = [ sum N_i*Yg_i(inf) + Nb*Ygb ] / M0
      Yg in 10^3 g.K/mol ; M0 = sum N_i*MW_i in g/mol  -> Tg in K.

  Nb / Ygb -- THE BACKBONE-IN-THE-SIDE-CHAIN TERM.
    `Ygb` (group `backboneSideChain`, SI row 58, Yg = 2.771) is the per-occurrence
    contribution `Nb` counts.  Nb = number of backbone atoms that sit in a SIDE
    chain (not on the main chain).  For the common vinyl polymers (PVC,
    polystyrene, poly(vinylpyridine), ...) Nb = 0, so the bracket is just
    sum N_i*Yg_i.  When a case has side-chain backbone atoms, add the group
    `backboneSideChain` with `count Nb` -- it is an ordinary additive term.

  GROUP IDENTITIES -- VERIFIED 2026-06-22.
    Table S3 draws each group as a 2D-structure IMAGE.  Rows S10-S11 (groups
    1-35) were matched to main-chain repeat-unit fragments and CROSS-VALIDATED
    against the paper's Fig 6: PVC (CH2 + CHCl) = 351 K, poly(4-vinylpyridine)
    (CH2 + CH4pyridyl) = 426 K, poly(N-vinylpyrrolidone) (CH2 + CH2pyrrolidinone)
    = 452 K, poly(N-vinylcarbazole) (CH2 + CHcarbazolyl) = 504 K -- all EXACT vs
    the paper.  Rows S12-S13 (groups 36-58) are the linker / aromatic / heteroatom
    groups, transcribed from the SI figures.

  *  Groups marked `vanKrevelen` in `provenance.note` carry an asterisk in
     Table S3 ("Group found in Van Krevelen's book"): the FW + Yg are reported by
     Yang 2020 (this is what we cite + redistribute), the structure originally
     catalogued by Van Krevelen.

  The engine REFUSES to write under data/standards/ -- editing this file is a
  CURATION act (see CLAUDE.md SS7).
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

groups
(
